    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>Get all your ingredients and equipment ready</p><p>Skim through these steps, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Equipment and pan sizes vary. Make sure you cook food thoroughly (even if it takes you a little longer than 10 min)</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/speedy-beef-bacon-and-red-wine-stew-with-crushed-potatoes/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now lets get started...</strong></p><p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>bacon lardons</strong> and <strong>mince </strong>to the pan and cook for 3 min or until beginning to brown, breaking up with a wooden spoon as you go</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/speedy-beef-bacon-and-red-wine-stew-with-crushed-potatoes/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>waxy potatoes</strong> to a heatproof bowl, then cover with <strong>cling film</strong> and pierce a few holes in the top with a fork</p><p>Put the bowl in the <strong>microwave</strong> for 6-8 min or until the potatoes are fork-tender</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/speedy-beef-bacon-and-red-wine-stew-with-crushed-potatoes/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and slice (don't chop!) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Once the mince and bacon have browned, crumble your <strong>baby button mushrooms</strong> roughly into the pan with your hands and cook for 3-4 min or until beginning to soften</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/speedy-beef-bacon-and-red-wine-stew-with-crushed-potatoes/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Chop your<strong> Tenderstem broccoli </strong>in half</p><p>Add your <strong>halved Tenderstem broccoli</strong> to a pot and cover with plenty of <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 3-4 min or until tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain and return to the pot and keep covered until serving</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/speedy-beef-bacon-and-red-wine-stew-with-crushed-potatoes/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Reboil a kettle</p><p>Once the mushrooms have softened, add your <strong>onion marmalade</strong> to the pan with your <strong>tomato paste</strong>, <strong>sliced garlic</strong> and 2 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tsp]</span> <strong>flour </strong>and<strong> </strong>cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/speedy-beef-bacon-and-red-wine-stew-with-crushed-potatoes/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>beef stock mix</strong> and <strong>red wine paste</strong> to the pan with 250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[325ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[425ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Gently stir it all together and cook for 2 min or until the sauce begins to thicken and the mince is cooked through (no pink meat!) \u2013 this is your <strong>speedy mince, bacon & red wine stew</strong></p><p>Once the potatoes are tender, add a generous knob of <strong>butter </strong>with a pinch of<strong> pepper </strong>and roughly crush with a fork \u2013 these are your <strong>crushed potatoes</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/speedy-beef-bacon-and-red-wine-stew-with-crushed-potatoes/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>speedy mince, bacon & red wine stew</strong> with the <strong>crushed potatoes </strong>and <strong>cooked broccoli </strong>to the side</p><p>Garnish with a generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
